description:
Coffee bar is my favorite coffee shop, my go to study spot, my home away from home... well, you get it. The reasons for why I love Coffee Bar are listed below: 

(1) tons of free non-restricted parking outside -- it's such a pain to have to feed your meter every hour and move your car every 2 hours as such is often the case in good ol' San Francisco; 

(2) plenty of tables and outlets & outside seating for when you want some fresh air -- note: there are ALWAYS tons of people here. Nonetheless, I've always been able to find a seat. Other pluses: free wifi and its not ridiculously noisy;

(3) their lattes and pastries are delicious. They have Vietnamese coffee too!! I haven't tried their sandwiches, salads, etc. but they look yummy from where I'm sitting right now; and

(4) it's clean and well-decorated. A restroom is available if you plan on being there for a while.

And, it's probably important to note that there are several tables here that are basically no-laptop zones from 11:30AM-2:30PM, understandably, for those looking to grab lunch/catch up with a friend.
